<title type="html"><![CDATA[10/29 (Thu.) 8 Ways to Build Good Habits and Break Bad Ones / How to Deal with Anxiety from Change (Host: Mark)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=440&amp;p=458#p458"><![CDATA[
<span style="color: #FF0000">Thursday gathering of Royal Club is relocated to Ikari 怡客咖啡, 台北市衡陽路116號</span><br /><br />Article 1: 8 Ways to Build Good Habits and Break Bad Ones<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.opencolleges.edu.au/informed/features/8-ways-build-good-habits-break-bad-ones/">https://www.opencolleges.edu.au/informe ... -bad-ones/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1. Can you set up an environment for yourself that favors you and makes it easier to build better habits?<br />2. Habits are the compound interest of self-improvement, please  Review and share whether you have good or bad habits that affect you.<br />3. Share some strategies or systems that help you do things.<br /><br />----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Article 2: How to Deal with Anxiety from Change<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://tw.voicetube.com/v3/videos/133770?fromPlatform=iOS&amp;linkSource=app&amp;utm_source=user-referral&amp;utm_medium=finish-play&amp;fromUser=697885">https://tw.voicetube.com/v3/videos/1337 ... ser=697885</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1. How do we reduce the anxiety?<br />2. Have you ever thought about your success, and who has helped you become successful? And why?<br />3. What comfort can you tell us? Please imagine and describe it to your relatives or friends.<br />4. Choose two or three question and share for everyone (PAPER 2).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=25437">Michael</a> — Sat Oct 24, 2020 7:53 pm</p><hr />
